DIPHTHERIA - PARAGUAY (02): BACKGROUND
***************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 15 Jun 2011
Source: GIDEON (Global Infectious Disease & Epidemiology Network)
[edited]
http://www.gideononline.com


Re: ProMED-mail Diphtheria - Paraguay: (Asuncion) alert 20110614.1814
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Notwithstanding an outbreak in 2002 [ProMED-mail post Diphtheria -
Paraguay (Central) 20020517.4239], diphtheria in Paraguay and
neighboring countries has been largely controlled since the 1980's.
(1,2) See graph at
http://www.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Diphtheria-SA.jpg.

Although decreasing rates have paralleled efficient implementation of
DTP [diphtheria, tetanus, pertussis] vaccination in the area,
immunization rates in Paraguay have been relatively low. (See graph at
http://www.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Diph-Vaccine.jpg).

References
----------
1. Berger SA: Infectious Diseases of Paraguay, 2011. 345 pp, 82
graphs, 906 references. Gideon e-book series.
http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-paraguay/.
2. Berger SA: Diphtheria: Global Status, 2011. 303 pp, 441 graphs,
259 references. Gideon e-book series.
http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/disease/diphtheria-global-status/.

